<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Beats Moya to Reach Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia beat
Spaniard Carlos Moya 7-6 (7-2), 7-6 (7-3) to reach the final of
the ATP Tour World Championship in Hanover, Germany on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian will battle for the title against world number one
and defending champion Pete Sampras, who eliminated Jonas Bjorkman
6-3, 6-4 in the other semifinals earlier.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov, ranked six in the world, only clinched a place in
the tournament last Sunday when he won the Kremlin Cup in Moscow,
his third title of the year.
</P>
<P>
The Russian is making his third straight appearance in the ATP
championship and has reached his first final in the event.
</P>
</TEXT>
