<HEADLINE> Arafat to Visit India Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) President Yasser Arafat is due to visit India
next week, Israel Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Arafat is to discuss with Indian leaders ways
of strengthening economic relations between the PNA and India, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian leader is expected to solicit help from India
to advance the peace talks between the Palestinians and Israel,
which face an impasse due to Israel's hardline policy.
</P>
<P>
India, operating a representation office in Palestinian
self-rule Gaza Strip, is a consistent supporter of the PNA, to
which it has so far pledged a 2-million-dollar aid package for
long-term economic development projects.
</P>
<P>
Arafat is in Switzerland today to meet with U.S. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright to explore ways to break the stalemate in
the peace process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
