<HEADLINE> S. Leone to Disarm Child Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 15 (Xinhua) -- While the military junta in
Sierra Leone is rejecting the demand for the disarmament of the
country's armed forces#,preparations are being made to deprive
armed children of their guns in the country.
</P>
<P>
The preparation came to high gear Friday when the junta held
a nationwide workshop on how to identify all child soldiers with
guns in Sierra Leone, prepare the documentation and registration
for their disarmament, demobilization and reintegration into the
society.
</P>
<P>
There are now about 5,000 below the age of 18 with guns in
Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
The 200 participants in the workshop are supposed to have
acquired skills of how to idenity children with guns before
returning to their respective districts to conduct the
decumentation exercise which is to start the coming Monday.
</P>
<P>
At the end of this exercise, a database will be established
in the Ministry of Social Welfare for the implementation program
to be carried out by international and local agencies including
the Catholic mission and Sierra Leonean Red Cross.
</P>
<P>
The whole exercise will help the authorities to get the right
information needed to speed up the disarmamenet of children with
guns and their reintegration into the society, a senior official
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
