<DOCNO> XIE19971116.0031 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Energy Resources Improving China's Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Rural areas in southwest China
are using new energy resources like methane and hydro-electric
power to help protect and improve the environment.
</P>
<P>
Methane is being used by 1,950,000 peasant households in
Sichuan province as the main fuel, accounting for a tenth of the
province's households.
</P>
<P>
Tibetan areas in the northwest part of the province need to pay
more attention to developing new energy resources, local experts
say. This area has 47 percent of the province's total acreage. Its
230,000 sq.km. are dry and cold and lack fuel.
</P>
<P>
The area should develop new energy resources like solar energy,
methane and hydro-electric power, which can also protect forests
and grasslands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
