<DOCNO> XIE19971116.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Computers Gain Popularity for Accounting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Computers have become a
popular tool for accounting for businesses in eastern China's
Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
So far, some 150,000 personnel in the field of accounting have
received certificates in computer use, said sources from the
provincial financial department.
</P>
<P>
One-third of the province's enterprises have adopted computers
to handle accounting and other management chores businesses. More
than 1,000 large and medium-sized firms completely depend on
computers for their accounting needs.
</P>
<P>
A commercial company in the province owning two markets and 11
branches has reduced its monthly expenses by 180,000-200,000 yuan
(22,500-25,000 U.S. dollars) since it adopted computers.
</P>
<P>
In the course of popularizing computers, Jiangsu has been
making efforts to develop software used in accounting. A group of
Sino-foreign ventures have applied software of this kind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
