<HEADLINE> Belarus Aims High at Industrial Productivity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Belarus should make remarkable
progress in next few years to improve the country's industrial
productivity, President Lukashenko said today.
</P>
<P>
The new industrial policy under the reform program of Belarus,
Lukashenko said, calls for enhancing the competitiveness of the
industrial sector at domestic and international marketplace.
</P>
<P>
Policy goals also include restructuring the sector, entry into
the world economic system, and integration with Commonwealth of
Independent States (CIS) economies, he told a meeting in Mogilev.
</P>
<P>
To secure their achievements, he was quoted as saying by an
Itar-Tass news agency report, new technologies are to be used,
exports expanded, and new price and investment policies formulated.
</P>
<P>
The president made the remarks before an audience attending a
national meeting on industrial development strategies.
</P>
<P>
Latest official statistics showed that Belarus' industrial
production in the first nine months this year was up 15.8 percent
over the same period last year. 
