<HEADLINE> Ill-Fated Palestinian Child Laid to Rest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 16 (Xinhua)-- The body of the nine-year-old
Palestinian child Ali Jawarish, who died of rubber bullet wounds
on Saturday, was laid to rest today in his hometown of the West
Bank city of Bethlehem.
</P>
<P>
Around 1,000 Palestinians participated in his funeral during
which anti-Israeli slogans were chanted, the Jerusalem Media and
Communication Center (JMCC) said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, dozens of Palestinian youths stoned the Israeli
military post near Rachel Tomb in Bethlehem and Israeli soldiers
responded by teargasing the youths, it added.
</P>
<P>
Ali was injured by rubber bullets in his forehead fired by
Israeli soldiers on Tuesday in Bethlehem while around 30
Palestinian children between the age of 8 to 12 throwning stones
at the Israeli soldiers in a area near the Rachel Tomb.
</P>
<P>
He was sent to a Jerusalem hospital for treatment but died on
Saturday due to the injuries.
</P>
<P>
Investigation by the Palestinian police has blamed the Israeli
soldiers for causing the death of the child, because they fired
the rubber bullets from a range of only 15 to 50 meters.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian police said the open fire regulations
concerning rubber bullets prohibit their use at a range closer
than 40 meters and these regulations also explicitly prohibit
shooting rubber bullets at children.
</P>
<P>
In the past ten years, 275 Palestinian children under the 16
have been killed by Israeli soldiers, of these 69 were under the
age of 12, Palestinian police said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
