<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Opens Senior Citizens Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Huzhou city in east China's
Zhejiang Province has opened a senior citizens residential area
spread over 1.67 hectares.
</P>
<P>
The complex is located in a beautiful scenic area in Nanxun
Township on the southern banks of Taihu Lake. The Jiu'an Public
Affairs Co.Ltd in the province has allocated over 16 million yuan
for construction of the complex since last October.
</P>
<P>
The complex includes a number of two- to three-storey
 building constructed in the ancient Chinese architectural
style. Said structures cover total floor space of over 15,000
square meters. The complex consists of apartment buildings, a
health center, recreational facilities, a conference hall and
various shops.
</P>
<P>
Reired teachers, low-rank officials, doctors, scientists and
employees of enterprises can apply for 68 apartments in the
complex.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Xide, general director of the Jiu'an welfare company, said
the complex will offer good living conditions and diversified
services in order to guarantee a happy life for senior
citizens. 
</P>
