<HEADLINE> UN Chief to Attend OIC Summit in Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 16 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Secretary
General Kofi Annan will attend the summit of the Organization of
the Islamic Conference (OIC) due to be held here in December, a
U.N. official announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian official news agency IRNA quoted head of the
U.N. office in Tehran Micheal Schulenburg as saying that officials
 from the U.N.-affiliated organizations including directors of the
U.N. Children's Fund (UNICEF) and the Food and Agriculture
Organization (FAO) would also take part in the OIC summit.
</P>
<P>
Terming that the U.N. and the OIC have close relations with
regular consultations and coordination, Schulenburg said one third
of the U.N. member nations have formed the OIC and officials of
the two organizations hold annual negotiations in Geneva over
major international issues.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the U.N. reform programs, he said discussion in
this respect continues and 51 members out of 185 members of the
U.N. are founding members of the world body, so they would be
given special status once a new reform plan is approved.
</P>
<P>
One should not forget that the U.N. is a very diverse
organization and it is very difficult to get all the countries to
agree on one thing, Schulenburg said, adding that discussions were
continuing in a very positive spirit.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that nations need collective agreements on ways
of solving global issues and to this end a framework is
needed, but the question is how these institutions can be made
more responsive and more effective. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
