<HEADLINE> Anhui Reports Record Grain Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, November 16 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province, one
of the nation's major grain producing areas, reported a record
1997 grain harvest of 28.5 billion kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Despite the adverse effects of flooding and drought on 120
million mu (one mu equals 0,067 hectares) of cultivated land, the
application of high technology and new strains of grain enabled
Anhui to increase its grain output by 1.5 billion kg on 1996.
</P>
<P>
The province introduced high-yield wheat to more than 4.75
million mu, with the per mu output 100 kg higher than that for
ordinary strains. Related efforts contributed greatly to the
record grain harvest, according to local sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
