<HEADLINE> Online Network to Link Clinics, Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, November 16 (Xinhua) -- China plans to establish an
online multimedia information network which will link doctors and
patients and provide distance learning capabilities.
</P>
<P>
The China Posts and Telecommunications Multimedia and
Information Technology Laboratory, which is establishing the
network, is based in Changsha, capital of central China's Hunan
Province.
</P>
<P>
The Changsha laboratory was jointly established in May by the
Hunan Posts and Telecommunications Science Research Institute,
Beijing Posts and Telecommunications University and China National
Defense University.
</P>
<P>
The lab has signed a number of cooperation agreements with
major foreign information technology companies, including
Microsoft and Motorola. PictureTel, an agent company, will supply
the network with state-of-the-art teleconferencing technology.
</P>
<P>
The network, will be China's largest online system linking
clinics and schools after completion in 1998.
</P>
<P>
The laboratory is also conducting extensive research into
technology which will enable users to book tickets, conduct
business activities and trade stocks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
