<HEADLINE> Causeway Bay Rated World's Top Rental for Shops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Causeway Bay, the bustling
downtown area in Hong Kong, has been rated the most expensive
retail real estate in the world, today's local papers quoted an
international survey as saying.
</P>
<P>
With a monthly rental up to 107 U.S. dollars per square foot,
Causeway Bay beat East 57th Street in New York, which came to the
second in the survey conducted by Healy &AMP; Baker, an international
real estate consultant company.
</P>
<P>
Trade House Cum in Moscow ranked the third, followed by
London's Oxford Street and Paris' Champs Elysees. Pitt Street in
Sydney is the most impressive new entrant into the top ten list,
securing the sixth place.
</P>
<P>
Causeway Bay, located in northern water front of the Hong Kong
Island, is a shopping destination both for local consumers and
foreign tourists. 
</P>
</TEXT>
