<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Makes progress in Telecom Sector: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina has said that her government had made some
encouraging progress in the telecommunications sector since it was
formed in June 1996.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina made the statement Saturday when
she addressed a function marking the formal inauguration of the
newly-constructed 2000-line digital telephone exchange in the
Southeastern city of Feni, according to local press reports today.
</P>
<P>
She said that the government would soon declare a national
telecommunication policy incorporating provisions for healthy
competition between the public and private sectors to ensure rapid
expansion of modern telecom system and better services to
subscribers.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the 90-million (about 2 million U.S. dollars)
exchange, the prime minister stated that the ultra-modern
telecommunications was an indispensable tool for the economic
development of the country.
</P>
<P>
With this telephone exchange, not only the telephone
communication would be eased and developed, but it would also
generate new life to the local administration particularly in
times of natural calamity and serve commercial and education
purposes.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said that during the past one and half
years, her government gave 160,000 new connections including
147,000 digital phones, and it is spending seven billion taka
(156.3 million dollars) for setting up such 14 new exchanges in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Besides, 200 new card phones were installed and new circuits
were added to 822 ISD and 5,116 NWD phones, she added.
</P>
<P>
For rapid expansion of the telecommunication service, her
government had given special thrust on the development of private
sector telecommunication network, she stated, adding that the
government had already given licenses to two rural phone
companies, four mobile cellular phone companies and one paging and
another radio-tracking company in the private sector.
</P>
<P>
During the last 25 year, only 350,000 telephone connections
were given across the country with a population of 120 million
while the present government gave 140,000 new connections all over
the country, according to Post and Telecommunications Minister
Mohammad Nasim. 
</P>
</TEXT>
