<HEADLINE> Former French Communist Party Leader Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Former General Secretary of the
French Communist Party Georges Marchais died this morning in
hospital at the age of 77 after his heart disease deteriorated this
weekend, said hospital sources.
</P>
<P>
Marchais, general secretary of the communist party from 1972
till 1994, had suffered from heart disease for more than 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Robert Hue, national secretary of the party, said that he was
greatly upset by the death of Marchais, who he said had given his
life to the party.
</P>
<P>
Born on June 7, 1920 in Hoguette in southern France, Marchais
was once a metallurgical worker and joined the party in 1947.
</P>
<P>
He was a parliament deputy representing Val-de-Marne near Paris
since 1973, and deputy of the European Parliament from 1979 to
1989. 
</P>
