<HEADLINE> 2 Killed, 20 Injured in Explosion in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 16 (Xinhua) -- At least two people were
killed and 20 others injured early today in India's Kerala state
in a high magnitude explosion which ripped apart a reinforced
concrete building where explosives and chemicals were allegedly
stocked unauthorizedly.
</P>
<P>
According to Press Trust of India (PTI), the explosion also
caused severe damage to adjacent multi-storeyed buildings,
including two hotels, in the city of Thrissur of the southern
Indian state.
</P>
<P>
Several vehicles, including a lorry laden with sulphur parked
in the premises, were either gutted or damaged in the explosion.
</P>
<P>
Official sources did not rule out the possibility of recovering
more bodies from the debris, which is spread over hundreds of
meters around the building where several people used to sleep
during the night.
</P>
<P>
The inhabitants of the area woke up on hearing the explosion,
which shook the entire area like an earthquake, PTI quoted
eyewitnesses as saying.
</P>
<P>
Local police and government officials have rushed to the spot
while search was on for people trapped under the debris.
</P>
<P>
The exact cause for the explosion remained unknown.  
</P>
</TEXT>
