<HEADLINE> Francophone Summit Ends in Hanoi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 16 (Xinhua) -- The three-day Francophone summit
ended here today with the election of former U.N. chief Boutros
Boutros-Ghali as the first secretary general of the Francophone
organization.
</P>
<P>
The 75-year-old Boutros-Ghali, who will become the political
speaker and coordinator of the organization, will hold the office
for four years.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese President Tram Duc Luong addressed the closing
ceremony, expressing his congratulations on the success of the
summit.
</P>
<P>
Three documents were adopted, urging all Francophone member
states to enhance cooperation in politics, economy, culture and
information.
</P>
<P>
It is decided that the next summit of the organization's member
states will be held in Canada in 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
