<HEADLINE> Cholera Afflicts More Victims in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, November 16 (Xinhua) -- The epidemic situation of
cholera has been worsening in the Mozambican capital Maputo since
September, local paper "Noticias" reported today.
</P>
<P>
In the past two months, up to 43 people have died of cholera,
and in the recent three days, 120 cholera patients
were admitted into Maputo Center Hospital, the report added.
</P>
<P>
With the number of cholera patients increasing in the capital,
the nursing staff in the hospital could not meet the demand. Thus
Mozambican Minister of Health Aurelio Zilhao has ordered the
closure of the Maputo Institute of Health Science for its
students to nurse cholera patients in Maputo Center Hospital.
</P>
<P>
Reacting to an appeal of the Maputo Bureau of Health, some
retired hospital nurses have reported for duty at concerned
departments to take part in the work of nursing cholera patients,
according to the report.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that neighboring Gaza Province has also
troubled with cholera, with about 40 victims but none of them
dead.
</P>
<P>
The report noted that hot weather, heavy rains, contaminated
water recently have led to the spread of cholera in Maputo and
Gaza Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
