<HEADLINE> Nepalese Woman to Bear 22nd Children in 27 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, November 16 (Xinhua) -- A Nepalese woman who got
married 27 years ago is going to give birth to her 22nd child in a
few months, The Kathmandu Post reported today.
</P>
<P>
The pregnant woman does not know what family planning is, the
newspapers said, adding the family planning programs have not
reach her village in western Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Her husband, a carpenter by profession, is also unaware of
family planning and temporary devices.
</P>
<P>
"We must receive with open arms what God is willing to give,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The population of Nepal, which stands at 21.4 million, is
growing at an alarming rate of 2.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The government is making efforts to operate clinics at villages
and provide contraceptives as more as possible to reduce the
fertility rate to four percent from 4.6 percent by 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
