<DOCNO> XIE19971116.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Plunges to New Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Continuing its downward
march for the third successive week, India's annual rate of
inflation fell to a new low of 3.23 percent during the week ended
November 1, Press Trust of India said today.
</P>
<P>
In the last three weeks, inflation, based on the wholesale
price index (WPI), has plunged by nearly a percentage point. The
fall, despite recent hikes in prices of petroleum products and
rail freight charges, is being attributed to slackening of demand
in the economy.
</P>
<P>
During the week under review, inflation fell by 0.22 percentage
points to 3.23 percent compared to 3.45 percent in the previous
week and 6.72 percent during the corresponding week last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the WPI for "all commodities" (base 1981-82=100)
declined marginally to 329.6 during the reference week from 329.7
the week before. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
