<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Companies Collaborate with Local </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen foreign companies in
collaboration with their local counterparts have registered with
Bangladesh's Board of Investment (BOI) during September this year,
the national news agency BSS reported here today.
</P>
<P>
The total investment of these projects will be around 15.66
billion taka (349.6 million U.S. dollars), BSS said.
</P>
<P>
The fields of activities of the proposed investment include a
cement plant based on cement clinker, garment accessories, cargo
carrying, edible oil, fuel filters for automobile and industrial
engines, trainer shoes, textile, assembling of four-wheelers,
passenger helicopter services, hotel and motel, and health
contraceptive, BSS added.
</P>
<P>
The foreign counterparts of the proposed projects are from
Iran, Korea, Jordan, Australia, the United States, Pakistan,
Taiwan, France, the United Kingdom, Hong Kong and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Out of the total proposed projects, over 6.8 billion taka (152
million U.S. dollars) will be invested by the firms from Jordan
and Australia along with their local counterpart, Chisty Airways
Limited for air cargo service.
</P>
<P>
Firms from Hong Kong and the United Kingdom will join their
Bangladesh counterpart, Sena Hotel and Developments Limited, for
establishing a four-star hotel with an investment of 86.21 billion
taka (192.4 million dollars) and an US-based firm will invest 6.22
billion taka (139.8 million dollars) as an independent power
producer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
