<HEADLINE> Spurious Liquor Claims 18 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen people, including
six women, died since Friday night after consuming spurious liquor
in India's Maharashtra State, the local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Sixty-two others have been admitted to hospitals in Bombay,
capital of the southwestern Indian state, for treatment and 10
were reported to be in critical condition. doctors feared more
deaths.
</P>
<P>
The police have launched a man-hunt for the suspect, a liquor
vendor identified as Mohammed Sheikh, who has been absconding
since the incident.
</P>
<P>
The liquor tragedy is the biggest to hit the state since
December 31, 1993, when nearly 100 people had died after consuming
hooch at a bar in Bombay.  
</P>
</TEXT>
