<HEADLINE> Major Shift of Military Personnel Announced in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, November 16 (Xinhua) -- A series of announcements for a
major shift of military personnel from high-level leaders to
regional commanders in myanmar were published today in all
official newspapers.
</P>
<P>
Of the 12 regional commanders including two newly-added ones,
commanders of Yangon, Central and Western regions retained the
posts while the other nine were newly appointed.
</P>
<P>
Commodore Nyunt Thein and Brigadier-General Kyaw Than were
respectively appointed as new commander-in-chief of the navy and
the air force. The two outgoing commanders-in-chief Vice-Admiral
Tin Aye and Lieutenant-General Tin Ngwe were respectively placed
in the newly-formed government cabinet as the minister for labor
and the minister for transport.
</P>
<P>
All of the regional commanders became members of the State
Peace and Development Council (SPDC), a new 19-member governing
body formed Saturday replacing the State Law and Order Restoration
Council (SLORC).
</P>
<P>
The SLORC was founded in September 1988 when it took over the
power of state.  
</P>
</TEXT>
