<HEADLINE> More Overseas Capital to Be Injected into China's Basic Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 16 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government will
continue to absorb direct overseas investment and loans to support
new agricultural techniques, energy, transportation, key raw
materials and other basic industries, according to a State
Planning Commission official.
</P>
<P>
Water conservation and environmental protection will take a
prominent position in the country's investment and construction
plans, said Song Mi, director of SPC's Department of Investment.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment will be an important source to fund China's
infrastructure that promises fast expansion in the next few years,
she was quoted by today's "China Daily" (Business Weekly) as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Overseas capital has been allowed to access most of the
infrastructure and basic industries by way of project financing, a
popular fund-raising method on the international capital market
for a project.
</P>
<P>
The practice is just beginning in China but regarded as a
promising market by overseas investors, Song said.
</P>
<P>
In the coming years, China will focus on comprehensive and
rational development of energy and transportation as well as post
and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
The official added that policies are being discussed to give
preferential tax treatment to infrastructure projects in central
and western areas of the country. 
</P>
