<HEADLINE> Vietnam, Romania Sign Debt Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and Romania signed an
agreement Saturday settling the debt dispute between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Under the Agreement on the Overall Treatment of Vietnam's Debt
to Romania, Vietnam will repay Romania's rouble debt in
U.S. dollars at favorable exchanging rates.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam will also repay the debt by goods.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was hailed as paving the way for further economic
cooperation between the two countries by Vietnam. The amount of
debt was not specified.
</P>
<P>
Prior to 1990, Vietnam borrowed large sums of money in roubles
from the former Soviet Union and Eastern European countries. In
recent years, the repaying process has been hampered by different
views on the exchanging rates of the rouble. 
</P>
</TEXT>
