<HEADLINE> China's Life Insurance Sector to Continue Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 16 (Xinhua) -- China's life insurance
industry will continue its strong momentum in the first decade of
the next century since rapid economic growth provides a solid
foundation for further development, a Chinese insurance company
manager predicted.
</P>
<P>
Shi Guoqing, vice-president of People's Insurance (Life) Co. of
China (PICC Life), said the market potential of the country's life
insurance industry will exceed 300 billion yuan ( about 36.1
billion US dollars) with life's share of 150 billion yuan by the
year 2000.
</P>
<P>
By 2010, gross premiums will reach 600 billion to 700 billion
yuan, of which 350 billion to 400 billion yuan will have been
obtained by life insurance, compared with 33 billion yuan in 1996,
Shi was quoted by today's "China Daily" (Business Weekly) as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The market will surely create a big cake for domestic and
overseas insurers, but only a few companies could have big bites,
he predicted.
</P>
<P>
"In the next decade, four to five big life insurance companies
will take 75 percent of the total market share," he said.
</P>
<P>
Now, there are nine domestic and overseas-funded life insurance
companies in China.
</P>
<P>
Among the 30.2 billion yuan premium volume in the first half
of this year, PICC Life accounted for 59.57 percent, Ping An 26.11
percent, the Pacific 11.3 percent, New China 1.37 percent and Tai
Kang 1.12 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
