<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Record Overseas Tourists Visited Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing, a
newly-designated municipality with a population of 30 million,
received about 200,000 overseas tourists in the first nine months
of this year, surpassing the record high in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Chongqing handled over 160,000 overseas tourists,
and earned about 100 million US dollars from international
tourism. The arrival of domestic tourists amounted to 16 million
and the earnings stood at 5.55 billion yuan (about 668 million US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Chongqing was separated from Sichuan Province to became China's
fourth municipality under direct administration of the central
government in March. Officials say the change can be attributed
partly to the growing tourist interest in the area.
</P>
<P>
Another reason for the rise in tourism is that increasing
number of visitors who flocked to see the Three Gorges of the
Yangtze River, where the world's largest hydro-electric Power
project is being built.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing now has 48 hotels catering to overseas tourists,
including 14 star-rated hotels, and 134 travel agencies.  
</P>
