<HEADLINE> Shanghai To Improve Environmental Protection Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 16 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's environmental
protection industry expects to have annual output value of 6
billion yuan (about 740 million US dollars) by the year 2000,
according to a municipal government plan.
</P>
<P>
Present annual output value of the industry is 2 billion yuan
(about 240 million US dollars), and a long-term goal is to raise
that to 40 billion yuan by 2010.
</P>
<P>
The city now has 50,000 people involved in research and
development, production, distribution, and information in the
environmental protection business.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government plans to establish a development fund
for the industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
