<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Casiraghi Makes Italy Through </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Italy book a late berth in World
Cup finals on Saturday in Naples, Italy, when they beat Russia 1-0
to take an aggregated 2-1 victory to make the 10th successive
qualification.
</P>
<P>
Pierluigi Casiraghi survived Italy's hope for their fourth
World Cup title with a 53rd minute winner, slashing a superb
left-foot shot from Demetrio Albertini's cross.
</P>
<P>
The Italians poured more efforts on Russia's goal while their
almost perfect defence smashed the Russians' hope for a draw to
carry the match into extra time.
</P>
<P>
Alongside with Yugoslavia, Croatia and Belgium, Italy completed
the qualifier list in the Europe zone for the World Cup finals. A
total of 28 countries have claimed their places in France World
Cup finals, with four more yet to be decided. 
</P>
