<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Poland to Promote Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kuchma
told Polish Foreign Minister Bronislaw Geremek here today that
developing relations with Poland is one of the issues Ukraine
would give top priority to.
</P>
<P>
Geremek, who arrived here today for a one-day visit to Ukraine,
said that the new Polish government would not change its policy
toward Ukraine which cannot but improve in the future, the
Ukrainian Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
After the talks with Vladimir Gorbulin, secretary of the
Ukrainian State Committee on Security and Defense, Geremek told
reporters that Poland would support Ukraine's integration with the
European security system.
</P>
<P>
Gorbulin said that a Ukraine-Poland-U.S. "strategic triangle"
would have a great prospect.
</P>
<P>
He described Geremek's visit as vital in view of the government
reshuffle in Poland at the end of last month. Ukraine was the
first country that the new Polish foreign minister paid a visit to.
</P>
<P>
At a joint news conference held with Geremek, Ukrainian First
Deputy Foreign Minister Anton Buteiko said the summit meeting of
the presidents of Ukraine, Romania and Poland scheduled for late
this month in Bucharest would help Ukraine direct its steps toward
the integration with Europe and NATO.
</P>
<P>
Geremek stressed the significance of his new government's
economic cooperation with its neighbor Ukraine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
