<HEADLINE> Croatia Reach World Cup Finals With 1-1 Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, November 15 (Xinhua) -- Croatia will make their first
appearance in the World Cup finals after they drew 1-1 with
Ukraine Saturday and qualifying 3-1 on aggregate.
</P>
<P>
The hosts made an early lead just four minutes into the match
from Andriy Shevchenko's drive in close range after Croatia's
goal-keeper Marijan Mrmic stopped Vitaly Kosovsky's effort.
</P>
<P>
But Croatians levelled at the 27th minute through Alen Boksic,
the Lazio forward, who stormed home a low right-foot shot.
</P>
<P>
After that equalizer, Croatia dominated the rest time of the
match. They had a good chance to win the match but Davor Suker
missed the scoring chance midway in the second half. 
</P>
</TEXT>
